column1: #Text=is in the state of Florida in the United States .
#Text=It includes Citrus , Hernando , Hillsborough , Manatee Pasco , Pinellas , Polk and Sumter counties .
#Text=- the largest city in West Central Florida .
#Text=The largest airport in the region is Tampa International Airport ( TPA ) on the western side of Tampa .
#Text=TIA serves dozens of destinations , with daily flights to most major cities in the US and almost every major airline hub .
#Text=The Tampa- Atlanta route carries the most passengers of any route with nearly 3 times as many passengers as the second largest destination Charlotte .
#Text=The largest airlines in/out of TIA are American , Delta , and Southwest .
#Text=Directly across the bay and just 10 miles from TIA is St. Petersburg-Clearwater International Airport ( PIE ) , which served mostly by budget airlines and used for private aviation .
#Text=It is a hub for Allegiant Air which flies to about two dozen small airports throughout the Midwest & Northeast .

#Text=As of February 2011 , it is also served by : Frontier Airlines to Milwaukee & Omaha ( both seasonal ) ; Air Transat to Halifax & Toronto ( both seasonal ) ; Sunwing Airlines to Toronto ; Vision Air to Gulfport-Biloxi ; & Locair to Marsh Harbour & Treasure Cay .
#Text=( SRQ ) is located between Sarasota and Bradenton and is served by American , Delta , JetBlue , and United .
#Text=About half of the routes are seasonal .
